-- Italy Needs Liberalization to Revamp Economy, Corriere Says
-- B y   C h i a r a   R e m o n d i n i
-- 2012-01-07T12:50:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-07/italy-needs-liberalization-to-revamp-economy-corriere-says.html
Italy needs to carry out market
liberalizations to revamp the economy, the country’s antitrust
chief Giovanni Pitruzzella told  Corriere della Sera .  “Liberalizations are an indispensable requirement to
restart the economy,” the newspaper cited the head of the
competition authority as saying in an interview. He added that
measures should be taken in industries including energy,
transports and banks, according to Corriere.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chiara Remondini in Milan at 
 cremondini@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
